name: NPR
text:
Phil Niekro, the National Baseball Hall of Famer and longtime pitcher for the Braves, has died at age 81.

From full-season debut in 1967 until his retirement in 1987, Niekro pitched 5,404 innings — the most by any pitcher in the modern era.
https://t.co/5XSA0kRckP

name: NPR
text: RT @HorsleyScott: By signing the COVID relief bill and related spending package, Pres. Trump has averted a government shutdown. But his cliffhanger delay has already cost millions of jobless Americans a week of unemployment benefits. name: NPR
text: The coronavirus relief package includes a fresh round of direct payments to qualifying Americans, worth up to $600 per adult and child; a boost in weekly unemployment benefits; and funds for small-business aid and vaccine distribution. https://t.co/LRbrhy20iN
